Team news 

Emmanuel Adebayor, Younes Kaboul, Mousa Dembele, Nacer Chadli and Danny Rose have all remained at home for Tottenham's Europa League clash at Partizan Belgrade.

The quintet have not travelled to Serbia for a variety of reasons, while a hip injury keeps full-back Kyle Walker out of the Group C encounter. 

Tottenham striker Roberto Soldado is in contention to face Partizan after recovering from injury

Roberto Soldado is in contention to lead the line at Partizan Stadium after recovering from an issue with his neck and back, while goalkeeper Michel Vorm and centre-back Federico Fazio could make their Tottenham debuts. 

Provisional squad: Lloris, Vorm, McGee, Naughton, Dier, Chiriches, Fazio, Vertonghen, Davies, Capoue, Stambouli, Veljkovic, Bentaleb, Mason, Paulinho, Eriksen, Lennon, Lamela, Townsend, Kane, Soldado.

